      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a Python function that calculates the Shannon entropy of a list of IP addresses using base 2 logarithms to handle floating point precision.\n\n```python\nimport math\nfrom collections import Counter\nfrom fractions import Fraction\n\ndef calculate_entropy(log_data):\n    # Count the occurrence of each IP address\n    ip_counts = Counter(log_data)\n    \n    totalropped = sum(ip_counts.values())\n    \n    entropy = 0.0\n    for count in ip_counts.values():\n        prob = Fraction(count) / totalropped\n        entropy -= prob * math.log2(prob)\n    \n    return entropy\n```\n\nThis function uses the `Counter` class from the `collections` module to count the occurrence of each IP address, then calculates the Shannon entropy using the entropycases equation with `math.log2` for base 2 logarithms. It also uses the `Fraction` class to avoid floating point precision issues. This should pass your test exactly.",
